before_they_were_stars.title: Before They Were Stars
before_they_were_stars.description: Back when they were just like us!

273066.title: Another Country
273066.description: In the 1930s, upper-class Tommy Judd and Guy Bennett are both nearing the end of their careers at their public school. Guy, when not mooning after pretty boys, angles for a slot as one of the "gods," or prefects, of his house.

273077.title: Shopping
273077.description: Billy and Jo are the leaders of a teen gang of "ram-raiders," car thieves who jack a car, ram it through the front of a store, and steal whatever booty they can carry before the cops arrive.

283899.title: Fire on the Amazon
283899.description: When a man is assassinated in the rainforest, a journalist and an activist team up to solve the case when they believe they’ve encountered a cover-up.

299580.title: The Big Easy
299580.description: A new female district attorney is unhappy with the gangs and corruption in New Orleans and bonds with a detective in this sultry crime thriller.

300165.title: Earth Girls Are Easy
300165.description: When three aliens crash-land in Los Angeles' San Fernando Valley, a manicurist and her boss befriend them, make them over and show them the town.

300839.title: Mystery Team
300839.description: A group of young detectives are challenged to crack a murder case and finally prove themselves as real detectives once and for all, in this comedy.

301152.title: Kalifornia
301152.description: While on a road trip researching for a book on serial killers, a writer and his photographer girlfriend get an unexpectedly hands-on education.

301348.title: The Night Before
301348.description: In this unusual teen comedy, the most popular girl in school embarks upon the worst date of her life after she loses a bet and is forced to attend the prom with the school's biggest nerd. The trouble begins when her doofus date gets lost en route and they end up stranded on the worst side of town.

301939.title: River's Edge
301939.description: A group of teenagers are thrown into a moral spin when one of them murders his girlfriend and they must decide whether to help him or turn him in.

302686.title: Disturbing Behavior
302686.description: The new kid in town stumbles across something sinister about the town's method of transforming its unruly teens into upstanding citizens.

303091.title: Johnny Be Good
303091.description: A high school jock is recruited by major colleges with the promise of free booze, willing cheerleaders, hard cash, and no homework in this comedy.

304372.title: The Crew
304372.description: Several friends on a weekend cruise, rescue two men from a burning boat, causing discord amongst them in this suspense thriller.

304799.title: The Bounty
304799.description: An idyllic voyage to Tahiti in 1789 turns a crew aboard the H.M.S. Bounty against its captain when they find tropical paradise and unlimited sex.

305014.title: The Falcon And The Snowman
305014.description: The true story about two childhood friends from affluent American families who betray their country when they decide to sell government secrets to the Russians.

305795.title: Best Men
305795.description: A group of friends' plan to help their pal get married after being released from prison goes awry when one of them is revealed to be a bank robber.

305818.title: Harley Davidson And The Marlboro Man
305818.description: Two modern-day "Robin Hoods" heist an armored car full of drugs, putting them in the sights of hired killers and on a ride for their lives.

306936.title: The Man In The Moon
306936.description: Set in the South during the 1950s, a fourteen-year-old girl comes to terms with one of life's most powerful yet fleeting feelings: adolescent love.

310151.title: Sleepover
310151.description: Before their freshman year in high school, four best friends have a slumber party that turns into a life-changing adventure.

312177.title: Force 10 From Navarone
312177.description: During World War II, several oddly assorted military experts are teamed in a mission to raid and destroy a bridge vital to enemy strategy, This sequel to The Guns of Navarone.

316454.title: Secretary
316454.description: Hoping to recover from her troubled past, a socially awkward woman becomes a secretary for an eccentric lawyer who is aroused by her obedience.

316460.title: Going Overboard
316460.description: A struggling young comedian takes a menial job on a cruise ship where he hopes for his big chance to make it in the world of cruise ship comedy.

321112.title: Bending All the Rules
321112.description: An ambitious photographer who doesn’t like commitment must choose between a striking DJ and a successful businessman in this romantic comedy.

321122.title: Hercules in New York
321122.description: When Zeus banishes Hercules to Earth, he decides to amuse himself by becoming a bodybuilder, but he struggles to adapt to life in New York City.

322160.title: Black Mama, White Mama
322160.description: Two women--one white, one black--escape from a women's detention camp in the Philippines...chained together.

323728.title: Zalman King's Red Shoe Diaries: The Movie
323728.description: After the suicide of his fiancée, a man reads her diary and learns she was having an affair.  He embarks on a journey to understand her.

326902.title: When Innocence is Lost
326902.description: Erica didn’t expect to be a mother at 17, but she desperately fights her baby’s paternal grandparents for custody in this movie based on a true story.

332937.title: Minotaur
332937.description: When the villagers offer their brethren as a sacrifice to the Minotaur, Theo sets off to the vast labyrinth intent on killing the evil bull-god.

334156.title: Mad Max
334156.description: A vengeful cop and a sadistic motorcycle gang face off in a chaotic wasteland.

369730.title: Igby Goes Down
369730.description: Born into privilege, a rebellious teenager longs for a life far from his schizophrenic father, self-absorbed mother, and conservative big brother.

376096.title: Guilt by Association
376096.description: Based on a true story, an innocent woman's life is derailed when she is  imprisoned for her boyfriend's wrongdoings and must fight to clear her name.

376176.title: Wildflower
376176.description: In this inspiring drama, two adolescents befriend a disabled girl to give her a fulfilling life despite the abuses of her stepfather.

382529.title: Streetwalkin'
382529.description: Straight from high school and into to the seedy world of sex work, young Cookie winds up answering to her new sadistic and murderous pimp, Duke.

385501.title: Cyborg 2
385501.description: In the year 2074, the PinWheel corporation creates a cyborg designed to charm her way into a rival manufacturer's headquarters and then self-detonate.

396732.title: Short Term 12
396732.description: Grace, a young supervisor at a foster care facility for at-risk teenagers, takes on the crises of two new residents while going through her own.

412222.title: The Kill Hole
412222.description: An Iraq War vet is forced to pursue one of his own into the Pacific Northwest wilderness to finally confront a war crime that has haunted them both.

413148.title: Girl
413148.description: An uptight high schooler abandons her sheltered life to be a groupie to a local rock singer, following his tour and making new friends on the way.

435809.title: The Falling
435809.description: A mysterious fainting epidemic disrupts life at a strict English girls’ school, where two best friends have begun to explore their sexuality.

447872.title: Jessabelle
447872.description: A young woman returns to her estranged father’s home after a traumatic accident and encounters a tortured spirit that wants to keep her there.

448257.title: Amores Perros
448257.description: A horrific car accident connects the lives of three strangers: a lovesick dog fighter, an injured supermodel and a hitman running from his past.

448827.title: Class
448827.description: A naïve prep-school boy enjoys one crazy night of passion, then discovers he has an alarming connection to the older woman who desires him.

449492.title: A Bear Named Winnie
449492.description: The true tale of an orphaned bear, adopted by a soldier on his way to fight in WW1, tracks the path of the cub that became A.A. Milne’s inspiration.

449515.title: Good Idea!
449515.description: A man who is sleeping with his re-married ex-wife baffles the police when he decides that kidnapping might work as a way of winning his beloved back.

449519.title: Without Evidence
449519.description: Based on the real-life murder of an Oregon corrections officer, a trail of lies and conspiracies defies the victim’s brother, who hunts for the truth.

460977.title: Royal Deceit
460977.description: A prince’s father is murdered by his brother, who then weds his widowed mother. The prince must now discover his power to regain his rightful throne.

461827.title: The Burning Plain
461827.description: A mother begins a dangerous love affair in a dusty border town while a restaurateur turns to sex in the aftermath of a childhood tragedy.

463798.title: High School U.S.A.
463798.description: A high-school senior butts heads with a rich-kid quarterback, as he tries to steal his rival's girlfriend and beat him in a drag race.

465249.title: Murder on the 13th Floor
465249.description: A negligent mother finds out that her husband is having an illicit affair with their live-in nanny and comes up with a deadly scheme for revenge.

465945.title: Hail Ceasar!
465945.description: A slacker singer makes a bet with his rich girlfriend's disapproving father. He has to make $100,000 in six months, or give her up forever.

466381.title: King Solomon's Mines
466381.description: A soldier of fortune embarks on a heart-pounding journey to help a clever young woman find her missing father, who got lost in the African jungle.

466812.title: Jackson County Jail
466812.description: A young woman in the mid-1970s falls into a nightmare land of hijacking and humiliation when she drives cross-country from California to New York.

466936.title: The Cry Baby Killer
466936.description: A terrified teenager takes three people hostage in a storeroom when he believes he's committed murder, leading to a tense police standoff.

466959.title: Bloodsucking Bastards
466959.description: A loser and a slacker who work at a bleak telemarketing company discover their new boss is a vampire who is turning their coworkers into bloodsuckers.

467933.title: Wish You Were Here
467933.description: The dark secret from an unforgettable vacation haunts a couple when they return home, leaving them to solve a disturbing family mystery.

468818.title: Escape From Polygamy
468818.description: Two teenagers trapped in the hold of an extreme polygamy sect must break from tradition and their beliefs to have a chance at being together.

469821.title: Fear
469821.description: A teenage girl’s dream crush on an older man, whom even her family approves of, turns terrifying when he reveals he’s an obsessed, psychopath stalker.

474070.title: We Are What We Are
474070.description: A reclusive family, who secretly follow ancient customs, risk exposure in their town as a torrential storm forces the daughters into survival mode.

475847.title: Teen Monster
475847.description: When a bunch of jocks accidentally kills a classmate, a brainy student resurrects the teen by transplanting the mind of a serial killer into his body.

475897.title: Girls Just Want to Have Fun
475897.description: A young gymnast with a strict father longs for the spotlight, so she and her free-spirited friend scheme to enter her in a TV dance show competition.

476644.title: The Boondock Saints
476644.description: Irish brothers try to clean up Boston’s underworld by knocking off gangsters and become local folk heroes, as an FBI agent traces their bloody trail.

478240.title: Sunburn
478240.description: A group of Irish college students are about to leave for the United States, where they've landed summer jobs on Long Island, New York. Working hard in the day and playing even harder at night, they relish the opportunity to enjoy adult life far from the eyes of their families. This will be a summer to remember for the rest of their lives.

478801.title: Return to Horror High
478801.description: A low-budget film crew investigate a series of unsolved murders at a high school, only to find themselves being hunted by that same killer.

486560.title: The Indian Runner
486560.description: Deputy sheriff Joe (David Morse) leads a simple life with his loving family. However, his idyllic existence abruptly changes when his troubled brother Frank (Viggo Mortensen) arrives at Joe's door. Much to the chagrin of his wife (Valeria Golino), Joe wants to help Frank make a better life, but soon discovers that this is a formidable task. As Frank continues his destructive behavior, Joe decides he's had enough, and they square off in a final showdown that pits blood against blood.

488778.title: Double Happiness
488778.description: A modern, young Chinese woman tries to bridge the gap between her own dreams and affections and the plans her traditional parents have for her life.

489706.title: Puncture
489706.description: A drug-addicted lawyer takes on the healthcare industry while battling his own personal demons in this legal drama based on a true story.

496403.title: The Curse of the Living Corpse
496403.description: It was supposed to be a family gathering of heirs in an old house for a reading of a will until the dead relative came back to life to kill them all.

497902.title: Return of the Killer Tomatoes
497902.description: This sequel to the cult classic follows a mad professor hellbent on world domination by mutating ordinary tomatoes into a machine gun-toting army.

500407.title: Ordinary Magic
500407.description: An orphaned teen moves to Canada from India and finds his new sense of home at risk by a land developer, so he turns to Hindu traditions to stop him.

505307.title: Disco Pigs
505307.description: An inseparable pair of friends with a bizarre connection start to see their relationship dynamic shift in a disturbing and violent way.

506264.title: Bright Young Things
506264.description: A look into the dramatic and cosmopolitan lives of young Londoners who kept the 1930’s tabloids running with their posh lifestyles and wild ways.

512252.title: We Need to Talk About Kevin
512252.description: In this suspenseful and gripping psychological thriller, a mother contends for years with the increasing malevolence of her first-born child, Kevin.

512448.title: New Jack City
512448.description: Two streetwise cops embark on the riskiest mission of their careers when they go undercover to bust a ruthless drug kingpin reigning over Harlem.

514069.title: The Locusts
514069.description: A young drifter, working for a widow on her cattle ranch, bonds with her taciturn son and falls for a local beauty, as a dark secret comes to light.

515861.title: The Magic Door
515861.description: Two children struggling to accept their new stepmother follow an exiled troll through a hidden door to a fairyland and embark on a wild adventure.

516695.title: Tuff Turf
516695.description: An East Coast, prep school teen moves to L.A. and ends up on the wrong side of a gang turf war while the gang leader’s girlfriend starts to like him.

520269.title: The Lair of the White Worm
520269.description: After a mysterious skull is unearthed near a convent, village residents start disappearing, and a pagan god hungers for the taste of virginal flesh.

523695.title: A Good Woman
523695.description: In the 1930s, a notorious seductress generates gossip on the Amalfi Coast, as she entices the wealthy American husband of a faithful young woman.

533717.title: Dummy
533717.description: After their mother passes away, Danny and Jack raise themselves. Danny escapes with sex and drugs, while Jack turns to a mannequin for guidance.

534023.title: Exposed
534023.description: While investigating the death of his partner, a cop finds proof of corruption within his police department and a troubled woman with a secret.

535796.title: The Deep Blue Sea
535796.description: A wealthy woman in a loveless marriage finds herself even more alone when she begins a stormy affair with a troubled ex-British Air Force pilot.

542040.title: The Babysitter's Seduction
542040.description: Michelle accepts a job babysitting for a wealthy couple. But after the wife of the family is found dead, Michelle becomes the number one suspect.

542299.title: Fifteen and Pregnant
542299.description: Drama about a 15-year-old girl who must lean on her mother, who is in the midst of a marital separation, after she discovers that she’s pregnant.

545105.title: Laws of Gravity
545105.description: Two petty crooks find the opportunity for a big score when an old friend and ex-con arrives in town with a load of illegal handguns for sale.

547110.title: Joyride
547110.description: After three aimless teenagers steal a car, they spark the anger of a deadly female assassin. Now they're in for the ride of their lives.

550824.title: The Hunger Games
550824.description: In a dystopian future, 16-year-old Katniss volunteers to take her younger sister’s place in a battle where children must fight to stay alive.

552742.title: The Fifth Floor
552742.description: When a disco dancer accidentally overdoses on drugs, she is wrongly diagnosed as suicidal and sent to an insane asylum full of unspeakable depravity.

552785.title: Still Breathing
552785.description: In search of the future wife he’s seen only in his “visions,” a goofy street puppeteer believes he’s finally found her, but she’s not all she appears.

559330.title: Attack the Block
559330.description: A teen gang must defend their neighborhood from savage aliens who turn their apartment complex into an intergalactic warzone.

560772.title: The War Zone
560772.description: Uprooted from big city life in London to rural Devon, a sullen teen boy struggles to adjust to his new life as he uncovers a shocking family secret.

563166.title: 28 Weeks Later
563166.description: Six months after the military declares Britain safe from the mysterious rage virus that ravaged the nation, a terrifying new nightmare soon begins.

564346.title: Bent
564346.description: After being forced by Nazi soldiers to murder his own boyfriend, a gay, Jewish man is sent to Dachau where, among the horror, he finds love once again.

564363.title: The Reflecting Skin
564363.description: Set in 1950’s Idaho, an eight-year-old boy from a troubled home becomes convinced the neighborhood widow is a secret vampire murdering his friends.

571541.title: My Brother the Pig
571541.description: A teen and her nanny rush to find an ancient antidote to break a spell that turned her brother into a pig just before he was pig-napped by a butcher.

571572.title: The Scapegoat
571572.description: A man who meets a man who looks exactly like him in a bar swaps lives with him, only to be drawn into the man’s scandalous life he can't quite escape.

571597.title: Exquisite Corpse
571597.description: A genius medical student faces a tragic decision when he decides to re-animate his dead girlfriend, which can only happen if someone else dies.

577525.title: Eden Lake
577525.description: A British couple takes a trip to a private and isolated lake quarry for a vacation, only to be targeted by a lurking mob of psychotic teenagers.

592664.title: The Miracle Season
592664.description: After their star player dies, a bereaved girl and tenacious coach lead their school volleyball team and town to victory, in this moving true story.

593866.title: Baby Boy
593866.description: The classic John Singleton film about a 20-year-old in South Central L.A. who loves like a man but isn’t stepping up in real life as a grown adult.

595396.description: Tells the story of how Spartan King Leonidas and his soldiers numbering just 300 beat King Xerxes of Persia, with an army of hundreds of thousands.

597264.title: All the Little Animals
597264.description: Christian Bale stars as a young man who flees his brutal stepfather and finds shelter with a kind man who helps him to finally confront the abuser.

599958.title: Maurice
599958.description: Set against the stifling conformity of pre-World War I English society, E.M. Forster's Maurice is a story of coming to terms with one's sexuality and identity in the face of disapproval and misunderstanding.

601959.title: Breathe In
601959.description: A British exchange student travels to Upstate New York, where her host family deals with a series of struggles, which she becomes entangled in.

604278.title: Gothic
604278.description: Lord Byron promises his guests a night of horror only a mad poet can deliver and after partaking in hallucinogens, the guests tell ghost stories while exploring the dark corridors of his home – and of their minds.

608869.title: Gone in a Heartbeat
608869.description: A suburban couple’s great life is torn when two thrill seeking teens kidnap the wife, who has a heart condition that will kill her if she’s not saved.

616506.title: Bring It On: In It to Win It
616506.description: Hot music, high-flyin' fun and no-holds-barred competition reach new heights when the East Coast Jets take on their rivals, the West Coast Sharks!

616516.title: Bring It On: All or Nothing
616516.description: When a popular cheerleader moves from her posh neighborhood to a working-class one, she soon finds herself at odds with her new classmates.

617447.title: Pretty Woman
617447.description: Julia Roberts stars as a witty prostitute who charms a serious businessman, as the two unlikely lovers fall for each other over the course of a week.

618615.title: Wills & Burke
618615.description: This historical parody centers on real-life Australian explorers William John Wills and Robert O'Hara Burke, who attempted to cross the continent.

622308.title: Make It Happen
622308.description: A small town dancer takes her dreams to a Chicago burlesque club, where she discovers a whole new side to herself through movement.

623323.title: Riot Girls
623323.description: When a mysterious disease wipes out all adults, two friends will stop at nothing to save one’s brother from savage jocks who rule half a town divided.

627766.title: Croupier
627766.description: Clive Owen’s star-making performance stuns as a writer who takes a job at a casino that begins to change his life and relationships for the worst.

629253.title: American Sausage Standoff
629253.description: Two dreamers aim to open the ultimate German sausage restaurant, to the chagrin of narrow-minded locals, who want to keep their small town ”American.”

630921.title: The Last House on the Left
630921.description: After their daughter is raped and left for dead, a couple exact bloody revenge on the attackers who have unknowingly taken shelter at their home.

631513.title: The People Under the Stairs
631513.description: Wes Craven lures you into the scariest house on the block in a chilling tale of a boy trapped in a home full of nightmarish inhabitants and creatures.

646863.title: BMX Bandits
646863.description: A trio of teen BMX enthusiasts finds themselves in the crossfires of a group of bank robbers after they sell their stash of walkie-talkies.

652270.title: The Goonies
652270.description: A pair of brothers hope to save their house by following a treasure map and taking their friends along on a subterranean sea adventure.

654066.title: Metroland
654066.description: After disappearing for ten years Toni suddenly reappears in London to bring chaos and doubt into Chris's quiet, peaceful, predictable life.

658082.title: To Die For
658082.description: Suzanne is dead set on being a famous TV reporter. When her husband asks her to give up her dream, she plots against him with a love-struck teenager.

659846.title: Waiting...
659846.description: A group of young employees at a chain restaurant ponder their lives while dealing with annoying patrons and staving off boredom with antics.

660761.title: Switching Parents
660761.description: Based on the true story of the boy who, after years of abuse, divorced his parents, with the aid of a lawyer and his wife, who decided to adopt him.

663313.title: Babes in Toyland
663313.description: Toyland is in danger of being destroyed by the evil Barnaby. Lisa, with the help of her family and friends, must drive the villain out of Toyland!

664881.title: Rolling Thunder
664881.description: After Major Charles Rane returns home from a POW camp, his wife and son are murdered. Rane teams up with his war buddy Johnny to get revenge.

665995.title: The Wild Ride
665995.description: Bad deeds finally catch up with a rebellious beatnik punk who spends his days as an amateur dirt track driver in between partying and troublemaking.

672456.title: Boy A
672456.description: A convicted child killer-turned-delivery man struggles to cope with the anger and fear of his community after a local newspaper learns about his past.

675219.title: Hi, Mom!
675219.description: A tale about a Vietnam vet, who peers through people's windows across the street, becomes obsessed with one of the women, and discovers Black theater.

675374.title: Dot the I
675374.description: A wavering bride, a stranger, an earnest groom: love triangle? Think again. The filmmaker adds many twists and turns to shape this romantic thriller.

676682.title: One & Two
676682.description: Imprisoned by their father on their family's property, two siblings with terrifying supernatural powers plot their escape and vengeance.

680198.title: In Secret
680198.description: A sexually repressed young woman embarks on an illicit affair with her husband's alluring friend in this smoldering thriller set in 1860s Paris.

680200.title: Lady Macbeth
680200.description: Lust, power, and murder collide in this thriller about the awakening of a young woman’s desire in rural England, 1865.

681184.title: Brotherhood of Justice
681184.description: High-school students start a vigilante group in their neighborhood but, as their power increases, they become more abusive and dangerous.

681769.title: Monster Party
681769.description: Three young thieves break into a Malibu mansion to save one of their fathers, unaware they’ve just wandered into a dinner party for killers.

681781.title: Chalet Girl
681781.description: After her mother’s tragic death, former skateboard champion Felicity Jones discovers love and snowboarding at an exclusive winter resort in Austria.

683835.title: Emerald City
683835.description: After making the move from Melbourne to Sydney, a scriptwriter and his wife are dazzled by the city lights while being tempted by lust and power.

683837.title: Erskineville Kings
683837.description: Two years after his escape from his abusive father, Barky hears that his father has passed away and believes it's finally safe to come home.

683839.title: Skin Deep
683839.description: Drama and tensions rise as two determined partners in a successful Australian fashion empire will stop at nothing to achieve individual success.

684141.title: Fish Tank
684141.description: A British 15-year-old aspiring dancer struggles with her mother’s immature ways, but finds herself drawn toward her mom’s boyfriend.

684169.title: The Killing Time
684169.description: A murderer assumes the identity of a new deputy in a coastal California town. But the sheriff and his lover are hatching a murder plot of their own.

690172.title: Just You and Me, Kid
690172.description: An impish retired vaudevillian takes in an unwanted foster child and teenage runaway who’s on the lam from the law and her drug dealer boyfriend.

690285.title: Like Minds
690285.description: A forensic psychologist is tasked with determining whether or not a student at a boy’s school should face murder charges for killing his schoolmate.

694768.title: American Pie
694768.description: The stakes are high when four friends make the pact to lose their virginity by prom night in this romp about high school, band camp and apple pie.

700714.title: Too Much Sun
700714.description: When their multimillionaire father dies, two gay siblings must find a way to produce an heir in order to inherit his fortune.

704506.title: The Sin Bin
704506.description: A teenage virgin finds himself mired in a love triangle after he starts lending out his van to his friends for use in their sexual encounters.

704869.title: Ca$h
704869.description: Two good guys are taken on a whirlwind ride to recover what lawfully belongs to someone else and wind up doing things they never would’ve imagined.

707359.title: Lovely & Amazing
707359.description: Self-esteem and insecurity lie at the heart of this comedy about the relationship between a mother and her three confused adult daughters.

709246.title: Timepiece
709246.description: In this prequel to the Christmas Box, a couple struggles with the tragic death of their only child against the backdrop of a turbulent World War II.

709254.title: Going All the Way
709254.description: After returning home from the Korean War, two young men discover love, fulfillment and the power of friendship in 1950’s middle America.

711136.title: How to Be a Player
711136.description: A playboy with a cool ride, a kickin' crib and a bomb job meets his undoing when all the women he’s secretly dating are invited to the same party.

714284.title: The Prince of Pennsylvania
714284.description: A misguided wannabe punk rocker desperate to free himself from the life his wealthy father planned for him finds his way out in a kidnapping plot.

714658.title: Power
714658.description: A high-priced political consultant able to make or break careers is forced to face the person he’s become and the corrupt people he’s gotten elected.

714835.title: Summer Heat
714835.description: A handsome drifter hired to assist with the harvest helps a Depression-era farm wife in a loveless marriage discover passion—but at a deadly price.

715449.description: In Middletown, at 11:14 PM, two car accidents happen simultaneously, affecting the lives of five different groups of people whose fates are connected.

716409.title: With Honors
716409.description: A homeless man holds a stuffy Ivy League student's misplaced graduate thesis hostage in return for room and board - one page for every day.

723250.title: Bend It Like Beckham
723250.description: Despite the wishes of their traditional families, two young women from different walks of life aim for a career in professional soccer.

723252.title: Mystery, Alaska
723252.description: When a publicity stunt brings the New York Rangers to a game with the local team, the town of Mystery rises to meet the challenge of a lifetime!

724108.title: Camp
724108.description: Based on a summer camp for young actors and performers, this film is a moving story of remarkable kids growing up and discovering who they are.

724157.title: The Little Shop of Horrors
724157.description: Seymour, a clumsy young man working at a flower shop, nurtures a plant and discovers it's carnivorous, forcing him to murder to feed it.

724421.title: The Vicious Kind
724421.description: A bitter, heartbroken man develops feelings for his younger brother's girlfriend, complicating an already uncomfortable family reunion.

724550.title: Cheerful Weather for the Wedding
724550.description: In this lighthearted romantic comedy, bride-to-be Dolly must choose between her devoted fiancee and the former lover she wants to seduce her.

724777.title: Frances Ha
724777.description: A late-20s New York woman dreams of being a dancer but is only an apprentice for a dance company. As she reaches adulthood, she finds herself.

100000082.title: Apartment 4E
100000082.description: A knock on the door from a stranger forces a reclusive suicidal woman to face a choice that will mean the difference between life and death.

100000171.title: Bohemian Rhapsody
100000171.description: Celebrates the rock band Queen, their music and their extraordinary frontman in the years leading up to their appearance at 1985's Live Aid concert.

100000266.title: Albatross
100000266.description: A brilliant, free-spirited teen disrupts a quietly dysfunctional family when she becomes entangled in an affair with her new best friend's father.

100001036.title: Carbon Copy
100001036.description: A straight-laced executive finds his comfortable life spinning hopelessly out of control when he meets the 17-year-old son he never knew he had.

100001150.title: Savage Grace
100001150.description: This story of forbidden passion tells of one of the most shocking scandals of the 20th century, the Barbara Daly Baekeland murder case.

100001360.title: Peace, Love & Misunderstanding
100001360.description: A high-strung lawyer decides to get a divorce and take her teenage kids upstate to Woodstock, NY to reconnect with her eccentric hippie mother.

100001408.title: One Crazy Summer

100001415.title: Critters 3
